latestIgtvVideos.title: How I spend time at Baga Beach in Goa! #goa #beach
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I have been to Goa so many time & still haven't been able to explore most of it. Goa might be small in size but the activities, monuments, culture & Goan life is so vast that you need at least 15 days to cover some of it. 

There are so many beaches in North Goa as a well as South Goa. North Goa beaches are commercial ones whereas South Goa untouched. 

In this video, I'm showing you things you can do around Baga beach in Goa. 

At Baga beach, you can do things ranging from peaceful walks to water sports & partying at shacks!. 

It's one of the most versatile beaches I have seen.

latestIgtvVideos.title: I visited @thepostboxvirar near VIVA college
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It is a must-visit if you love some good food & ambiance. 

It is a delight to step into The Post Box Virar! As you enter you come across an installation of what I think are hundreds of glass bottles on your left & on your right you will see bags of letters giving you a feeling of '80s!

We ordered black lollipop, it is made with chicken tossed in garlic & soy sauce. 
Later we ordered Gujju favourite pizza, which is a half & half pizza. One side is veg & another side has smokey pulled chicken. 
For the main course, we order a stir fry sizzler which was a party for tastebuds. It was loaded! It has noodles, veggies, chicken, sauces, eggs & did I say more chicken? 

Totally worth it! 

Google Location: https://goo.gl/maps/jMiK5GMSFHdX6L1L9
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: When was the last time you went cycling? 🚴
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Last weekend me and my friends decided to cycle to a lake in Juhandra. It was very pretty, however we were lost &  somehow we found our way to this beautiful lake. Honestly, I don't even know if it's the lake we were searching for, because it did not look anything like what we saw in the pictures, but that does not mean it was not pretty, it was beautiful!

This little lake is located a little away from Chandika mandir in Juchandra! Juchandra is overall a very unexplored place it's filled with many such gems.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Dining @thepostofficebistrobarvasai post lockdown  Is it safe?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Tag your gang with whom you want to dine-in asap 😎

Before visiting I had certain questions in my mind:
- Is dine-in safe?
- Are the restaurants take all precautions?
- Should I go to a restaurant to dine in or opt for take out?

Well, in this video you can see how my experience was!

 The Post Office Bistro & Bar is a place where I often go with my friends & with my family. Going back there was really nostalgic. The food was mind-blowing as you can see & the service was spectacular! 

I found it to be very safe, considering all the precautions they are taking. 
However, if you still are skeptical about dining out, I totally respect that. You can order in because you just can't miss out on the delicious food they offer.
.
.
.
.

All set to relive old memories at the 90‑year‑old Good Luck Café in Pune, the same place I once rushed through for Bun Maska & Chai without truly enjoying it.

These days I just want to slow down… savor the food, the people, the conversations.
But life had other plans! After a long rickshaw ride we discovered the café is shut.

And yet, the day turned out beautiful. We found another café, sat for hours, chatted about everything and nothing, and made new memories. 💛
